column1: #  ADF&G 2011 trawl survey Haul data   # Haul_rate : r (retow), d(bad tow)

column31: Sticky bottom last half of tow
Terminated tow at 0.8nmi, observed unfavorable bottom ahead of vessel, mudded down on haul back; 30 minutes to get net on board.
Soft bottom last half - towed slightly faster; retow @ 5 legal RKC
Strong ebb current - did not attempt parallel tow
Ended tow early- rocks and mud - no problems
NW 10 knts - New tow path start 300' N of station. Hung at 0.73 nmi, start this tow, same heading 0.4 nmi earlier.
New tow path - no problem, stems current well.
Stem? strong current - 1.5 Kt+, difficult tow. Starboard trawl door mudded in last 0.2nmi.
Maneuvering first 0.5 nmi to clear commercial pot gear.
Delayed start, repair coupling link on door legs.
20' tear on foot fr/ mid pt of stbd wing back into body of net. Probably should drop this station.
Catching rocks, stopped early @ 0.81nmi. 540+ pound rock, no damage to net.
bad trawl; not to count in survey; 20'+ tear fr/ beginning of wing to middle of headrope, primarily along headrope. Several 3-12 bar holes in vicinity of tear.
Start tow 0.43nmi ESE of station center point b/c of problems in previous years
Good tow Paralleled old path through center point.
N03; probably should repeat this tow; extensive damage due to large rocks (from email)
N04; stopped tow early .8NM suspected rocks and debris; some net damage (from email)
